"{\"uid\": \"cnalifestyle.channelnewsasia.com-entertainment-tom-cruise-paris-olympics-closing-ceremony-handoff-los-angeles-394446\", \"text\": \"Entertainment  Entertainment  The Mission: Impossible actor's segment is said to be intended as a handoff to\\u00a0Los Angeles, the next host city.  Cast member Tom Cruise attends the world premiere of Mission: Impossible - Dead Reckoning, at Via della Conciliazione, in Rome, Italy, June 19, 2023. (Photo: Reuters/Guglielmo Mangiapane/File Photo)  This audio is generated by an AI tool.  Tom Cruise may just be at the Paris Olympics for another reason, other than rooting for Team USA. According to The Hollywood Reporter, the alleged plan is to have the Mission: Impossible star skydive during the closing ceremony on Aug 11.  The segment is planned as a handoff to\\u00a0Los Angeles, the next host city.  According to TMZ, the 62-year-old actor and producer will allegedly be featured taking the Olympic flag with him from the State de France stadium.  It is said to then cut to a two-minute, pre-recorded segment of the Top Gun star hopping onto a plane and flying to LA, where he will jump out of the plane and land on the Hollywood sign.  The stunt that took place at the Hollywood sign, according to TMZ, was already quietly shot in March this year.  The Hollywood Reporter learned that another flag-handoff stunt involving a large party at Will Rogers State Beach was pulled as LA's police was hesitant to shut down Pacific Coast Highway to shoot the pre-recorded segment.  Subscribe to CNA's Recommended Read  A single handpicked story that we think you should not miss. Just one a day.  Copyright\\u00a9 Mediacorp 2025. Mediacorp Pte Ltd. All rights reserved.  We know it's a hassle to switch browsers but we want your experience with CNA to be fast, secure and the best it can possibly be.  To continue, upgrade to a supported browser or, for the finest experience, download the mobile app.\"}"